<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS INTERNATIONAL MODEL ES52-7A AND ESO65-7A 6-PLUS - REASSEMBLY - SHIFT TOWER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SHIFT TOWER</title>
        <para>Refer to Illustration.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To reassemble the tower, first position the yoke onto the shift lever. Secure the yoke by
                pressing the pivot pin into position.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the lever assembly into the tower housing. NOTE: The raised boss on the yoke must be
                placed next to the side of the tower that contains the casting number stamp.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the two trunion screws. Torque to 100-125 ft. lbs.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the boot into place. Secure it with two tie cables, being careful not to cut into the
                boot.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
